        public SchemaNotDefinedException(java.lang.Throwable t)
        Construct a new SchemaNotDefinedException wrapping an existing exception.

        The existing exception will be embedded in the new one, and its message will become the default message for the SchemaNotDefinedException.

        Parameters:
        t - nested Throwable

      • SchemaNotDefinedException

        public SchemaNotDefinedException(java.lang.String message,
                                 java.lang.Throwable t)
        Create a new SchemaNotDefinedException from an existing exception.

        The existing exception will be embedded in the new one, but the new exception will have its own message.

      • SchemaNotDefinedException

        public SchemaNotDefinedException(java.lang.String error,
                                 java.lang.String suggestion,
                                 java.lang.Throwable t)
        Create a new SchemaNotDefinedException from an error text, suggestion text and existing exception.

        The error and suggestion being set here is used later to prepare well formatted exception message based on resource bundle key 'msg_with_suggestion' and 'msg_no_suggestion'.

        Parameters:
        error - ResourceBundle message key, or a plain text message containing error details.
        suggestion - ResourceBundle message key, or a plain text message containing hints to solve the error.
        t - Throwable object t can be provided at the time of calling following constructor.
